                    p Publicly, candidates always make announcements like “When  I’m President, I will ___(fill-in-the-blank)___ on Day One.”
                    p They never say “If I become President.” It’s always “When.”  Even with twenty other candidates running for nomination,  each will project that they are the one who will win.
